.TH NICE 1
.SH NAME
nice \- run a command at low priority
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B nice
[
.BR \- increment
]
command [ arguments ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.I Nice\^
executes
.I command\^
with a lower
.SM CPU
scheduling priority.
If the
.I increment\^
argument (in the range 1-19) is given,
it is used;
if not, an increment of 10 is assumed.
.PP
The super-user may run commands with
priority higher than normal
by using a negative increment,
e.g.,
.BR \-\-10 .
.SH SEE ALSO
nohup(1).
.br
nice(2) in the
\f2\s-1UNIX\s+1 System V Programmer Reference Manual\fR.
.SH DIAGNOSTICS
.I Nice\^
returns the exit status of the subject command.
.SH BUGS
An
.I increment\^
larger than 19 is equivalent to 19.
